c: 28
v: 38
t: "And here addressed Pharaoh his peers: \"O you peers of the realm\", he said, \"I never knew an Ilah to whom you pay reverence and veneration but myself. Therefore, bake for me O Haman -his grand vizier- the moulded bricks of clay with fire and erect for me a lofty building soaring skyward, I might find the means of mounting to the Ilah of Mussa whom I deem a great liar"